President Obama has nominated John A. Gibney for a seat on the United States District Court, Eastern District of Virginia. Gibney is a civil litigator and has more than 30 years of practice in Richmond, Virginia. He has represented businesses, local governments, constitutional offices, and private individuals in various matters in state and federal courts. Gibney started his legal career as a law clerk to Justice Harry L. Carrico of the Supreme Court of Virginia and later served as an Assistant Attorney General of Virginia. He graduated from the College of William & Mary and the University of Virginia School of Law. President Obama believes that Gibney is a dedicated public servant with an excellent record of excellence and integrity, and he is confident that Gibney will serve the people of Virginia with distinction.